<subSubSection id="02C66578FFFCFFBDFF3D9ACF69C67A40" pageId="17" pageNumber="31" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFCFFBDFF3D9ACF68707BA2" blockId="17.[151,756,1675,1825]" pageId="17" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFCFFBDFF3D9ACF68057BC2" bold="true" box="[151,264,1675,1699]" pageId="17" pageNumber="31">Remarks:</emphasis>
It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="8DDC4D70FFFCFFBDFE1E9AC86B257BC2" box="[436,552,1675,1699]" class="Globothalamea" family="Eggerellidae" genus="Dorothia" kingdom="Chromista" order="Textulariida" pageId="17" pageNumber="31" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="bulletta">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFCFFBDFE1E9AC86B257BC2" box="[436,552,1675,1699]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="31">D. bulletta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in being a conical shape and larger size.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFCFFBDFF3D9A8E69C67A40" blockId="17.[151,756,1675,1825]" pageId="17" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFCFFBDFF3D9A8E68D87B83" bold="true" box="[151,469,1738,1762]" pageId="17" pageNumber="31">Stratigraphic distribution:</emphasis>
